parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel speed sensors can cause the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) to engage at slow speeds, leading to reduced vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The ABS system engages at low speeds
the vehicle's brakes grab or pulse
the vehicle feels as though it will not stop
premature wear on brake linings and shoes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear on brake linings and shoes can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Cracked brake linings and shoes
premature wear on brake pads and rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tread Separation on Copper Discovery A/T Tires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tread separation on Copper Discovery A/T tires can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Tread separation
loss of tire pressure
vibration while driving
noise while driving
damage to the vehicle's body or suspension.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel tank leak can cause fuel to spill onto the road, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents or injuries. Additionally, fuel leaks can lead to engine stalling, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions.
symptoms: Strong fuel odors inside or outside the vehicle
fuel droplets or puddles under the vehicle
engine stalling or difficulty starting
decreased fuel efficiency.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed fuel pump can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or stranding the driver. Additionally, fuel pump failure can lead to fuel leaks, increased emissions, and decreased fuel efficiency.
symptoms: Engine stalling or difficulty starting
decreased fuel efficiency
whining or grinding noises from the fuel pump
fuel leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can reduce visibility during rainy or snowy weather, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wipers stop working
windshield wipers operate intermittently
windshield wipers leave streaks or residue on the windshield
windshield wipers do not clear the windshield effectively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seatbelt retractor can cause the seatbelt to retract at an angle and speed that can result in injury to the passenger, including facial bruising and potentially more severe harm.
symptoms: The rear seatbelt retracts at an angle
the rear seatbelt retracts too quickly
the passenger is struck in the face or body by the seatbelt
the passenger experiences bruising or other injuries due to the seatbelt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt buckle cable can cause the buckle to detach from the belt, rendering the seatbelt ineffective and increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The cable that holds the buckle to the belt breaks
the buckle detaches from the belt
the seatbelt is no longer secure
the occupant is not properly restrained.
